WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:05.200
Hello and welcome back. In this lesson, I will show you what to do if you make a mistake in

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:10.480
the setup of OpenClaw or if you want to make changes to existing configurations.

00:00:11.360 --> 00:00:18.080
Just open a new command line terminal and type in the command openclaw onboard. Use the arrow

00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:28.000
key and select yes, then hit enter. Choose either quick start or manual. I will choose manual. Here,

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:34.240
if you want to make changes to the configuration choose update values then hit enter

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:42.640
do not change anything leave it at local gateway this machine just hit enter accept the default

00:00:42.640 --> 00:00:50.480
workspace directory just hit enter now you can add additional model provider or you can update

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:56.560
api keys for existing provider if you do not wish to change anything but wish to keep the existing

00:00:56.560 --> 00:01:02.640
model you have previously configured, just scroll down and select skip for now.

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:05.680
Here choose the model you previously configured.

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.540
For me, I choose OpenAI Codex.

00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:13.960
Here is where you can change to a different model if you want to, but I will keep current

00:01:13.960 --> 00:01:18.100
model which is GPT 5.4 and hit enter.

00:01:18.100 --> 00:01:23.240
I will keep the default port and just hit enter.

00:01:23.240 --> 00:01:29.600
Next I will also keep the default gateway bind to loopback and just hit enter.

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:34.460
I will keep the gateway auth to token, just hit enter.

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:40.300
I will leave tail scale exposure to off, just hit enter.

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:44.080
Select the default generate plaintext token, just hit enter.

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:50.040
It will show the token, I will keep it, so I hit enter.

00:01:50.040 --> 00:01:55.180
Next if you want to add another chat channel for example discord or whatsapp or others

00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:56.580
choose yes.

00:01:56.580 --> 00:02:01.800
For me I already configured telegram previously and I do not wish to add another channel for

00:02:01.800 --> 00:02:06.400
now so I will choose no then hit enter.

00:02:06.400 --> 00:02:10.160
Here you can add additional search provider if you wish.

00:02:10.160 --> 00:02:14.780
Previously I already added tavily search and do not wish to add another so I choose

00:02:14.780 --> 00:02:18.700
skip for now and hit enter.

00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:23.660
Next, you can add new skills for OpenClaw if you wish, and you could browse the list

00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:29.440
of skills by going to clawhub.ai and selecting the name of the skill you want to add.

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:34.960
At the moment, I do not need to add any new skills, so I will choose no.

00:02:34.960 --> 00:02:40.660
For plugins, press spacebar to select skip for now and hit enter.

00:02:40.660 --> 00:02:46.180
For hooks, I had previously already enabled all hooks and do not wish to make any changes,

00:02:46.180 --> 00:02:50.500
So I press spacebar to select skip for now and hit enter.

00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:55.380
I select yes to install gateway service and hit enter.

00:02:55.380 --> 00:03:02.420
For gateway service runtime, just accept the default which is node and hit enter.

00:03:02.420 --> 00:03:07.920
Gateway service already installed, select the restart and hit enter.

00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:14.180
Just accept the default enable zsh shell completion for openclaw and hit enter.

00:03:14.180 --> 00:03:15.800
Onboard completed.

00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:20.000
So this is how you make changes to configurations the easy way.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:23.480
We just use the command: openclaw onboard.

00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:30.140
You can now chat with openclaw by using the command: openclaw dashboard or use telegram.

00:03:30.140 --> 00:03:31.140
That's all for this video.

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:31.960
Thanks for watching.

